verify(string, set) returns the position of the first character
in string that is not in set. It returns 0 if all characters are in set.

string = [ abc123 ]
  verify(s, 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz') = 4
  verify(s, '0123456789') = 1
string = [ abcdef ]
  verify(s, 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz') = 7
  verify(s, '0123456789') = 1
string = [ 12345 ]
  verify(s, 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz') = 1
  verify(s, '0123456789') = 6
string = [ abc def ]
  verify(s, 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz') = 4
  verify(s, '0123456789') = 1
string = [ ABCdef ]
  verify(s, 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz') = 1
  verify(s, '0123456789') = 1
string = [  ]
  verify(s, 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz') = 1
  verify(s, '0123456789') = 1

direct examples:
verify('abc123', 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz') = 4
verify('abcdef', 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz') = 0
verify('12345',  '0123456789') = 0
verify('abc def', 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz') = 4

back=.true. searches from the right:
verify('abc123abc', 'abc')              = 4
verify('abc123abc', 'abc', back=.true.) = 6

case-sensitive examples:
verify('ABCdef', 'abcdef') = 1
verify('ABCdef', 'ABCdef') = 0
